---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
		title="Privacy Policy"
		description="Our privacy policy: We don't collect, track, or store any personal data. No cookies, no analytics, no tracking."
>
	<div class="page-content">
		<div class="container-narrow">
			<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

			<div class="highlight-box">
				<p><strong>TL;DR:</strong> We don't collect any data. Period.</p>
			</div>

			<section class="content-section">
				<h2>What We Don't Collect</h2>
				<ul class="privacy-list">
					<li>❌ No cookies</li>
					<li>❌ No analytics or tracking pixels</li>
					<li>❌ No user accounts or personal information</li>
					<li>❌ No IP address logging</li>
					<li>❌ No third-party scripts or services</li>
					<li>❌ No advertising networks</li>
					<li>❌ No social media trackers</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="content-section">
				<h2>How This Site Works</h2>
				<p>
					This is a fully static website hosted on AWS Amplify. When you visit a page:
				</p>
				<ol>
					<li>Your browser requests the page from AWS's servers</li>
					<li>AWS sends the HTML, CSS, and minimal JavaScript</li>
					<li>Your browser displays the page</li>
					<li>That's it. Nothing is logged, tracked, or stored.</li>
				</ol>
				<p>
					The only data AWS Amplify may collect are standard web server logs (IP addresses,
					request URLs) which we do not access or analyze. These logs are automatically
					deleted after a short retention period per AWS's policies.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="content-section">
				<h2>Search Functionality</h2>
				<p>
					The recipe search feature runs entirely in your browser using JavaScript.
					Search queries never leave your device. We don't see what you search for.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="content-section">
				<h2>Email Contact</h2>
				<p>
					If you email us (via the mailto links on this site), standard email privacy
					applies. We'll only use your email address to respond to your message and
					won't share it with anyone else.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="content-section">
				<h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
				<p>
					If we ever change this policy (spoiler: we won't, because there's nothing to
					change), we'll update this page with the date of the change.
				</p>
				<p><strong>Last updated:</strong> November 2025</p>
			</section>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

